            <abstract id="ref4" label="Abstract ">One green SoundScriber phonograph disc, indicated in corresponding as "Record 3." Contains the end of "The Buffalo Story," which was presumably begun on prior two discs, which are not in the collection and not known to exist anymore. The remainder of the disc contains the story "Geneseo Reservation" in its entirety, followed by an unidentified story in Chinese. Recorded by Charles F. Voegelin in 1946.</abstract>
